        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>American long rifles [300037183], rifles (long guns) [300037181], long guns [300222278], small arms by form [300037156], small arms [300037150], firearms [300037148], projectile weapons with explosive propellant [300208782], projectile weapons [300203727], armaments [300420324], weapons [300036926], Weapons and Ammunition (hierarchy name) [300036743], Furnishings and Equipment (hierarchy name) [300264551], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Heavy, long-range, muzzleloading rifles designed for use on the western frontier of the United States, approximately from 1800 to 1870. Typically they were unornamented, made with browned or dull metal that did not gleam in the light, and fitted with percussion locks and double-set triggers.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Rifles pesados de largo alcance, cargados por la boca, usados en la frontera Oeste de los Estados Unidos, aproximadamente desde 1800 a 1870. Por lo general no tenían ornamentos, eran fabricados en metal bronceado u opaco para que no brillara con la luz, y estaban provistos de llaves de percusión y doble juego de gatillos.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Zware, voorladende geweren met een groot bereik die werden ontwikkeld voor gebruik in het westen van de Verenigde Staten, globaal tussen 1800 en 1870. Meestal hadden ze geen versieringen, waren ze gemaakt van gebruineerd metaal en uitgerust met percussiesloten en dubbele trekkers.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
